{"lemma":"حُسْنُ","slug":"حُسْنُ","root":"ح.س.ن","root_slug":"ح-س-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-س-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حُسْن","root":"حسن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":13},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":30},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8000","n8007","n8008","n8010"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become good, to better, to improve"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become pleasant or agreeable"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become pleasant or agreeable; to be or become beautiful, to beautify","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to improve, to ameliorate, to better, to polish, to embellish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perfect"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prettify, to beautify, to adorn, to make attractive"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bedeck, to ornament, to decorate, to deck out, to garnish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shape up, tidy up (hair or beard)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to apply cosmetics, to put on makeup"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to amend"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fake"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَسُنَ (ḥasuna) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"goodness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prettiness, beauty, loveliness, shapeliness, comeliness, gorgeousness, pulchritude"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"handsomeness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"charm, charms, glamor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"glory"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nicety, fineness, grace, gracefulness, foppery"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fineness, efficiency, efficacy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"good, fine, well"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"agreeable, pleasant, nice, well-favored"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pretty, beautiful, lovely, comely, sightly, shapely, gorgeous, fair"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"handsome, good-looking, magnificent"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"well-turned"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"radiant, glad, charming"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"graceful, fine, dainty"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"okay, all right"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"Hasan, acceptable"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Hasan or Hassan"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Ḥasan ibn ʕaliyy, the grandson and a revered companion of Muhammad, and the 2nd Shia Imam."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Causative form II verb derived from the form I verb حَسُنَ (ḥasuna, “to be good”)."},"ipa":["/ħa.san/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8000","headword_ar":"حَسُنَ","root":"Hsn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.,) which may also be written and pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasona","text_ar":"حَسْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the dammeh suppressed, (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasana","text_ar":"حَسَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonN","text_ar":"حُسْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, K, * TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonaY","text_ar":"حُسْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ham p. 657, and Bd in ii. 77,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, S, Msb),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessed, the quality termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasonN","text_ar":"حَسْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see below; i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(generally the latter,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautiful, comely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHs~n","text_ar":"تحسّن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"often signifies the same, as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHs~n Einodahu","text_ar":"تحسّن عِنْدَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his estimation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K, TA:) and [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosana","text_ar":"اَحْسَنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd became possessed of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huson","text_ar":"حُسْن"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mughnee in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  One may not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Husona","text_ar":"حُسْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", transferring the dammeh of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":"and making the former letter quiescent, except in one case; because it is [virtually, together with its agent expressed or implied, in this case,] a predicate: [see I'Ak p. 234:] this is allowable only in the case of a verb of praise or dispraise;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Husona","text_ar":"حُسْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in respect of the transference of the medial vowel, being likened to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEoma","text_ar":"نِعْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biy^osa","text_ar":"بِيْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which are originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEima","text_ar":"نَعِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bay^isa","text_ar":"بَيِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and thus one does in all verbs like these two in meaning: a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lamo yamonaEi Aln~aAsu min~iY maA A^aradotu wa maA\n                      \n                     \n                        A^uEoTiyhimu maA A^araAduwA Husona *aA A^adabaA"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"[Men have not withheld from me what I have desired, nor do I give them what they have desired: good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very good, is this as a mode of conduct!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasuna h`*aA A^adabFA","text_ar":"حَسُنَ هٰذَا اَدَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasuna zayodN","text_ar":"حَسُنَ زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very good"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is Zeyd!"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosino","text_ar":"اَحْسِنْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is Zeyd!"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aHosanahu","text_ar":"مَا اَحْسَنَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (B, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n8007","headword_ar":"حُسْنٌ","root":"Hsn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusunN","text_ar":"حُسُنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is of the dial. of El-Hijáz, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[generally the latter,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beauty, comeliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasingness; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quboHN","text_ar":"قُبْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAlN","text_ar":"جَمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) but accord. to As, [when relating to the person,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonN","text_ar":"حُسْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in the eyes, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAlN","text_ar":"جَمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in the nose: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"symmetry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"just proportion of the several parts of the person, one to another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything, moving the mind, that is desired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wished for; such as is approved by the intellect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is approved by natural desire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is approved by the faculty of sense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the common conventional language, mostly applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is approved by the sight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur, mostly to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is approved by mental perception:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is in accidents as well as in substances: (Er-Rághib, TA:) the pl. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAsinu","text_ar":"مَحَاسِنُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaAmiHu","text_ar":"مَلَامِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamoHapN","text_ar":"لَمْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAbihu","text_ar":"مَشَابِهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abahN","text_ar":"شَبَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c., (Har p. 9,) contr. to rule, (S, K,) as though pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHosanN","text_ar":"مَحْسَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHosanN","text_ar":"مُحْسَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S accord. to different copies:) or, accord. to Lh"},{"kind":"page_break","n":571},{"kind":"text","text":"and Eth-Tha'álibee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAsinu","text_ar":"مَحَاسِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has no proper sing. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa quwluwA liln~aAsi HusonFA","text_ar":"وَ قُولُوا لِلنَّاسِ حُسْنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [ii. 77], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And say ye to men a saying having in it goodness"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawolFA *aA HusonK","text_ar":"قَوْلًا ذَا حُسْنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonFA","text_ar":"حُسْنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"may mean"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanFA","text_ar":"حَسَنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Zj, TA:) and some read here"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanFA","text_ar":"حَسَنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": and some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusunFA","text_ar":"حُسُنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the dial. of El-Hijáz: and some, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonaY","text_ar":"حُسْنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an inf. n., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu$oraY","text_ar":"بُشْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Bd:) but AHát and Zj disallow this; the former saying that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonaY","text_ar":"حُسْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolaY","text_ar":"فُعْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEalu","text_ar":"اَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"denoting the comparative and superlative degrees], and therefore should have the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa waS~ayonaA AlA_inosaAna biwaAlidayohi HusonFA","text_ar":"وَ وَصَّيْنَا الاـِنْسَانَ بِوَالِدَيْهِ حُسْنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxix. 7], means [in like manner]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we have enjoined man to do to his two parents what is good"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHosunu HusonFA","text_ar":"يَحْسُنُ حُسْنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (TA:) and here [also] some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanFA","text_ar":"حَسَنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHosaAnFA","text_ar":"اـِحْسَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Bd.) [See another ex. of a similar kind, from the Kur xviii. 85, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_im~aA","text_ar":"اـِمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the beginning of the paragraph.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~u AlHusoni","text_ar":"سِتُّ الحُسْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The convolvulus caïricus"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.; abundant in the gardens of Cairo;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant that twines about trees and has a beautiful flower."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["MF","TA","S","K","Kull","Zj","Bd"]},{"entry_id":"n8008","headword_ar":"حَسَنٌ","root":"Hsn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing, the quality termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonN","text_ar":"حُسْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see above;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(generally the latter,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautiful, comely, pleasing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (Msb, K, TA;) either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intrinsically,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as when applied to belief in God and in his attributes; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extrinsically,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as when applied to war against unbelievers, for this is not good in itself: said to be the only epithet of its measure except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTalN","text_ar":"بَطَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasiynN","text_ar":"حَسِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, (IB, K,) because from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasuna","text_ar":"حَسُنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZiymN","text_ar":"عَظِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karyimN","text_ar":"كَريِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZuma","text_ar":"عَظُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karuma","text_ar":"كَرُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IB, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusaAnN","text_ar":"حُسَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) but this is an intensive epithet, [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] (IB, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hus~aAnN","text_ar":"حُسَّانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) also an intensive epithet, (S, IB,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAsinN","text_ar":"حَاسِنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [properly signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becoming, good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] cited by Lh as used in a future sense, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHas~anN","text_ar":"مُحَسَّنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as applied to a face: (K:) the fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanapN","text_ar":"حَسَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasonaA='u","text_ar":"حَسْنَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman, (S, Msb, K,) though the corresponding masc. of this latter, namely, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosanu","text_ar":"اَحْسَنُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", is [said to be] not used (S, K) as applied to a man [in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S,) [but the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^aHosanuhumo wajohFA","text_ar":"هُوَ اَحْسَنُهُمْ وَجْهًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasanuhumo wajohFA","text_ar":"حَسَنُهُمْ وَجْهًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is mentioned in the S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byD","text_ar":"بيض"},{"kind":"text","text":", (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayaADN","text_ar":"بَيَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and see also the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAsinu","text_ar":"اَحَاسِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in what here follows,)] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hus~aAnapN","text_ar":"حُسَّانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) the pl. masc. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HisaAnN","text_ar":"حِسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"used as an epithet; but when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a [proper] name, its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasanuwna","text_ar":"حَسَنُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HisaAnN","text_ar":"حِسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may also be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasiynN","text_ar":"حَسِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hus~aAnuwna","text_ar":"حُسَّانُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, K,) pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hus~aAnN","text_ar":"حُسَّانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has no broken pl.: (Sb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAsinu Alqawomi","text_ar":"اَحَاسِنُ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HisaAnuhumo","text_ar":"حِسَانُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the party,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) the pl. fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HisaAnN","text_ar":"حِسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) like the masc., pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasonaA='u","text_ar":"حَسْنَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the only instance of its kind except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EijaAfN","text_ar":"عِجَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajofaA='u","text_ar":"عَجْفَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN basanN","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ بَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man very good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], using"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bsn","text_ar":"بسن"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an imitative sequent [for the purpose of corroboration]. (S.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN HasanN","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tradition of good authority;"},{"kind":"text","text":"generally applied to one transmitted in the first instance by two or more relaters. ―         -b3-  Also meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good, comely, goodhumoured, pleasing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant, discourse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talk."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHasanu","text_ar":"الحَسَنُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bone that is next to the elbow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHusonu","text_ar":"الحُسْنُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the extremity of the bone of the upper half of the arm next the shoulder-joint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the abundance of flesh that is upon it; the extremity of that bone next the elbow being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqabiyHu","text_ar":"القَبِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qbH","text_ar":"قبح"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the upper part of that bone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the lower part thereof being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqbyH","text_ar":"القبيح"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr, TA in that art.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of tree, of beautiful appearance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"also called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alA='","text_ar":"اَلا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that grows in rows upon a hill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyb","text_ar":"كَثِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because of its beauty; whence the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kvyb","text_ar":"كثيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaA AlHasani","text_ar":"نَقَا الحَسَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus described by Az, on the authority of 'Alee Ibn-Hamzeh. (TA.) ―         -b6-  [And hence, perhaps,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A high"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyb","text_ar":"كَثِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heap, of sand"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IAar, K:) whence it is used as a [proper] name of a boy. (IAar, TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonN","text_ar":"حُسْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":["TA","IB","K","S","Msb","Sb","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n8010","headword_ar":"حُسُنٌ","root":"Hsn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonN","text_ar":"حُسْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}